I've build a [custom turbopack loader](https://github.com/vitalets/turbopack-inline-svg-loader) that conditionally inlines SVGs as data URIs, based on the file size. It works in Next.js 16+, that introduced turbopack *condition rules*.

Configuration:
```js
const nextConfig = {
  turbopack: {
    rules: {
      '*.svg': {
        loaders: ['turbopack-inline-svg-loader'],
        condition: {
          content: /^[\s\S]{0,4000}$/, // <-- Inline SVGs smaller than ~4Kb (since Next.js v16)
        },
        as: '*.js',
      },
    },
  },
  // ...
};
```
