If you are passing `pathname` to a router push or replace method, I suggest you pass `asPath` from the router object instead of `pathname` when you have to navigate the user to a path that has query/params.

In my case, I had this error when I was trying to change the locale using `router.push(...)`, I passed `pathname` as the first parameter to that method, I fixed it by doing this:
```ts
  conat router = useRouter()
  const { asPath, pathname, locale, push } = router

  const handleChangeLocale = async (locale: string) => {
    push(asPath, undefined, { locale }) // this one works
    // passing pathname instead doesn't work and returns your error
    // because the placeholders weren't replaced with their values yet.
  }
```

