Here's how I've set up my `next.config.js`:

```diff
+ /**
+  * Flip this to `true` whenever you want to watch changes in
+  * node_modules (e.g. to debug a dependency).
+  * 
+  * It's expensive to watch node_modules all the time, so make
+  * sure to put it back to `false` once you're done debugging.
+  * 
+  * @see https://github.com/vercel/next.js/discussions/34380#discussioncomment-8936245
+  */
+ const watchNodeModules = false;
  
  /**
    * @type {import('next').NextConfig}
    * @see https://nextjs.org/docs/pages/api-reference/next-config-js
    */
  const nextConfig = {
    // ... unrelated stuff...

+   webpack: (config, { isServer, nextRuntime }) => {
+     if (watchNodeModules) {
+       // It's recommended to opt-out of managedPaths if editing files in
+       // node_modules directly.
+       // @see https://github.com/webpack/webpack/issues/11612#issuecomment-705790881
+       // @see https://webpack.js.org/configuration/other-options/#managedpaths
+       config.snapshot.managedPaths = [];
+
+       // config.watchOptions isn't directly writable, so we use defineProperty.
+       Object.defineProperty(config, "watchOptions", {
+         ...Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(config, "watchOptions"),
+         value: {
+           ...config.watchOptions,
+           ignored:
+             /^((?:[^/]*(?:\/|$))*)(\.(git|next))(\/((?:[^/]*(?:\/|$))*)(?:$|\/))?/,
+         },
+       });
+
+       // This seems to work without any changes to watchOptions.followSymlinks
+       // or resolve.symlinks, but in case it ever becomes relevant:
+       // @see https://github.com/webpack/webpack/issues/11612#issuecomment-1448208868
+     }
+ 
+     return config;
+   },
  };
  
  module.exports = nextConfig;
```

It's based on changing the original `config.watchOptions.ignored` to cut out the `node_modules` exclusion:

```diff
- /^((?:[^/]*(?:\/|$))*)(\.(git|next)|node_modules)(\/((?:[^/]*(?:\/|$))*)(?:$|\/))?/
+ /^((?:[^/]*(?:\/|$))*)(\.(git|next))(\/((?:[^/]*(?:\/|$))*)(?:$|\/))?/
```

Caution 1: If that Regex ever updates in a future version of Next.js, make sure to log `config.watchOptions.ignored` to identify its new value, then cut out the part of the rule that excludes `node_modules` again.

Caution 2: If you find that you are making changes and they're still not getting picked up, check that you're editing the right file. In my project, Webpack traverses only the MJS sources and disregards all CJS ones.

