I've found a workaround if you're using a custom server, albeit it's somewhat hacky and not guaranteed to work in future versions.

```ts
type ExposedNextServer = Omit<NextServer, 'getServer'> & {
  getServer: () => Promise<ExposedNextServer>;
  quiet?: boolean;
};

async function createNextServer() {
  const server = next({}) as unknown as ExposedNextServer;
  const innerServer = await server.getServer();

  if (!(innerServer.logError instanceof Function)) {
    throw Error('Expected NextServer.logError to be a function');
  }

  innerServer.logError = (err: Error) => {
    if (innerServer.quiet) return;
    logger.error(err, 'NextJSError');
  };

  return server;
}
```

All said and done, this logError implementation is the [exact same as what exists in NextJS currently](https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/eb629c15ca55c247d216963a16abc1bea60d7f91/packages/next/server/base-server.ts#L436), with the logger method replaced

