Received this error when using RecoilJS. Also causes page to fully hang / not load on refresh.
The fix was to use `useRecoilValueLoadable` (async) instead of `useRecoilValue` (sync) since there was an API call setting default value.

You may need to put that under `useEffect` (not necessary), in that case:
```typescript
export const useCustomHook = ({ ...input }) => {
    const myValue = useRecoilValueLoadable(recoilAtomFamily(input));
    const myValueRef = useRef(myValue);

    useEffect(() => {
        if (myValue.state === 'hasValue') {
            myValueRef.current = myValue.contents;
        }
    }, [myValue, input]);

    // Return a default value
    if (!Array.isArray(myValueRef.current)) return [];

    return myValueRef.current;
};
```

