In your case, I think it's better to use a custom _app along with next/head and next/router instead of a custom document, because _document only works on the server side, not the client side (so any next updates won't update your href attribute of the tag links). I think you should try do something like this:
`// your custom _app.js:`
```
import Head from 'next/head';
import { useRouter } from 'next/router';

function MyApp({ Component, pageProps }) {
  const router = useRouter();

  return (
    <div>
     <Head>
         <link rel="test" href={router.basePath} />
     </Head>
      <Component {...pageProps} />
    </div>
  )
}

export default MyApp
```
